        <num>CCP 1037</num>
        <heading>1037.  Action instituted separately</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1037.  Action instituted separately
When a person does not assert in an incidental demand the action which he has against a party to the principal action or a third person, he does not thereby lose his right of action, except as provided in Article 1113, and except as provided in Article 1061.</p>
        </content>
